{"nodes": [{"id": "2026_06_09_keybinding_discovery_popup_design_document", "label": "Design", "file_type": "document", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-09-keybinding-discovery-popup/design.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "2026_06_09_keybinding_discovery_popup_design_context", "label": "Context", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-09-keybinding-discovery-popup/design.md", "source_location": "line 1", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "`pi-vimmode` currently uses one-row transient/workbench feedback for runtime discovery. `:actions`, `:keymap`, `:mapcheck`, `:features`, `:help`, and `:messages` are finite, read-only Ex surfaces that preserve prompt state and avoid Vim parity claims. Recent action-keybinding work added richer metadata:"}, {"id": "2026_06_09_keybinding_discovery_popup_design_goals_non_goals", "label": "Goals / Non-Goals", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-09-keybinding-discovery-popup/design.md", "source_location": "line 16", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "**Goals:** - Make `:features keybindings` open a dedicated bordered/readably separated overlay popup, not plain inline Ex/workbench rows."}, {"id": "2026_06_09_keybinding_discovery_popup_design_decisions", "label": "Decisions", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-09-keybinding-discovery-popup/design.md", "source_location": "line 39", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "### Decision: Add popup state with panel-local scroll offset, not a retained message Target seams: `src/modal/types.ts`, `src/modal/state.ts`, `src/modal/core.ts`, `src/modal/engine.ts`, `src/modal/ex-command-line.ts`, and `src/vim-editor.ts`."}, {"id": "2026_06_09_keybinding_discovery_popup_design_decision_add_popup_state_with_panel_local_scroll_offset_not_a_retained_message", "label": "Decision: Add popup state with panel-local scroll offset, not a retained message", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-09-keybinding-discovery-popup/design.md", "source_location": "line 41", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Target seams: `src/modal/types.ts`, `src/modal/state.ts`, `src/modal/core.ts`, `src/modal/engine.ts`, `src/modal/ex-command-line.ts`, and `src/vim-editor.ts`. Use a small state shape such as `helpPopup?: { title: string; lines: readonly string[]; source: \"features\"; query: \"keybindings\"; scrollOffset: number; docsAnchor: string }`. Treat popup display and scroll offset as transient UI state like workbench feedback, but keep it separate from `ExMessage` and `messageHistory` so `:messages` remains"}, {"id": "2026_06_09_keybinding_discovery_popup_design_decision_route_only_selected_discovery_commands_to_popup_in_m1", "label": "Decision: Route only selected discovery commands to popup in M1", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-09-keybinding-discovery-popup/design.md", "source_location": "line 54", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Target seam: `src/modal/ex-command-line.ts` runtime-help branch. M1 should route `:features keybindings` to popup state. Other `:features` queries and `:help`/`:actions`/`:keymap` should keep existing one-line messages unless separately required later. This keeps compatibility and blast radius tight while proving the display model on the known cramped use case."}, {"id": "2026_06_09_keybinding_discovery_popup_design_decision_build_popup_content_from_existing_metadata_helpers", "label": "Decision: Build popup content from existing metadata helpers", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-09-keybinding-discovery-popup/design.md", "source_location": "line 66", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Target seams: `src/action-keybinding-recipes.ts`, `src/runtime-help.ts`, `src/customization.ts`, `src/config.ts`, and `src/keybinding-discovery-popup.ts`. The formatter returns structured title/lines for keybinding discovery. It should reuse existing recipe/preset metadata, resolved `keymap.actions.accepted`, bindable prompt transform action entries, diagnostic/help metadata limits, and protected shortcut catalog notes."}, {"id": "2026_06_09_keybinding_discovery_popup_design_decision_render_a_dedicated_bounded_overlay_popup_with_actionable_scroll_indicators", "label": "Decision: Render a dedicated bounded overlay popup with actionable scroll indicators", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-09-keybinding-discovery-popup/design.md", "source_location": "line 86", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Target seams: `src/vim-editor.ts` and maybe `src/render.ts`. Render the popup as a dedicated Pi TUI overlay, visually separated from Ex/workbench feedback. The overlay has a title/header, footer, and border treatment so it is not perceived as the Ex command-line section increasing in height. It should float above existing terminal content rather than append rows to the editor render output."}, {"id": "2026_06_09_keybinding_discovery_popup_design_decision_popup_local_scroll_keys_are_handled_before_normal_vim_input", "label": "Decision: Popup-local scroll keys are handled before normal Vim input", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-09-keybinding-discovery-popup/design.md", "source_location": "line 108", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Target seams: `src/modal/engine.ts`, `src/modal/core.ts`, and modal tests. When popup is visible, popup input handling runs before normal/visual/editor command handling. At minimum, `j`/`k` and arrow-down/arrow-up scroll one row within the popup. `g`/`G` may jump top/bottom if cheap. Unsupported printable keys should be ignored while the popup is visible rather than leaking into prompt edits. `Esc` and delegated reset/cancel behavior should dismiss the popup. Protected Pi shortcuts should preser"}, {"id": "2026_06_09_keybinding_discovery_popup_design_decision_dismiss_through_existing_reset_cancel_paths_and_preserve_read_only_invariants", "label": "Decision: Dismiss through existing reset/cancel paths and preserve read-only invariants", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-09-keybinding-discovery-popup/design.md", "source_location": "line 123", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Target seams: `src/modal/engine.ts`, `src/modal/core.ts`, and modal tests. When popup is visible, `Esc` and delegated reset/cancel keys should clear popup state. Dismissal must not edit text, move cursor, clear registers/marks/macros/search history, change dot-repeat, or append message history. Existing protected Pi shortcut ownership should remain intact; if a reset key already delegates to Pi after clearing state, preserve that behavior where appropriate."}, {"id": "2026_06_09_keybinding_discovery_popup_design_decision_drift_guard_popup_docs_and_output_anchors", "label": "Decision: Drift-guard popup docs and output anchors", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-09-keybinding-discovery-popup/design.md", "source_location": "line 134", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Target seams: `docs/features.md`, `test/docs-drift.test.ts`, `openspec/specs/runtime-help-drift-guard/spec.md`, and focused runtime tests. Docs should explain the dedicated overlay, what appears, how to scroll, how to dismiss, and what is intentionally absent. Runtime tests should verify representative output rather than snapshotting every line."}, {"id": "2026_06_09_keybinding_discovery_popup_design_ref_src_action_keybinding_recipes_ts", "label": "action-keybinding-recipes.ts", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-09-keybinding-discovery-popup/design.md", "source_location": "line 7", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "2026_06_09_keybinding_discovery_popup_design_ref_src_prompt_transform_actions_ts", "label": "prompt-transform-actions.ts", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-09-keybinding-discovery-popup/design.md", "source_location": "line 8", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "2026_06_09_keybinding_discovery_popup_design_ref_src_diagnostic_actions_ts", "label": "diagnostic-actions.ts", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-09-keybinding-discovery-popup/design.md", "source_location": "line 9", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "2026_06_09_keybinding_discovery_popup_design_ref_src_customization_ts", "label": "customization.ts", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-09-keybinding-discovery-popup/design.md", "source_location": "line 10", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "2026_06_09_keybinding_discovery_popup_design_ref_src_runtime_help_ts", "label": "runtime-help.ts", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-09-keybinding-discovery-popup/design.md", "source_location": "line 11", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}], "edges": [{"source": "2026_06_09_keybinding_discovery_popup_design_document", "target": "2026_06_09_keybinding_discovery_popup_d